<subSubSection id="C30B655C4B098132BEB16E6FFCF295A8" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAE36D74B098132BEB16E6FFCF295A8" blockId="2.[151,1437,638,953]" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BEB16E6FFE899560" bold="true" box="[199,313,855,881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Remarks.</emphasis>
The epithets 
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BFAE6E6FFD919560" box="[472,545,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">dubius</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BC2B6E6FFD149561" box="[605,676,855,880]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">roseus</emphasis>
(both originally combined to 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D544B098132BD886E6FFB229560" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1840" box="[1022,1170,855,881]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Phyllophoridae" genus="Phyllophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dendrochirotida" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BD886E6FFB229560" box="[1022,1170,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Phyllophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, gender masculine) are adjectives which must be brought into agreement with the feminine grammatical gender of 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D544B098132BAEF6E43FA8C9584" authorityName="Heding &amp; Panning" authorityYear="1954" box="[1177,1340,891,917]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Phyllophoridae" genus="Phyllophorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dendrochirotida" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BAEF6E43FA8C9584" box="[1177,1340,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Phyllophorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D544B098132BEE16EA7FE3595A8" box="[151,389,927,953]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Phyllophoridae" genus="Phyllophorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dendrochirotida" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BEE16EA7FE3595A8" box="[151,389,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Phyllophorella dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D544B098132BFCD6EA7FD1695A9" box="[443,678,927,953]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Phyllophoridae" genus="Phyllophorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dendrochirotida" pageId="2" pageNumber="561" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rosea">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B098132BFCD6EA7FD1695A9" box="[443,678,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="561">Phyllophorella rosea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
